Module Hierarchy

  • sqltriples: A simple SQL-accessible RDF triple store.

Class Hierarchy

  • __builtin__.object: The most base type
    • __builtin__.basestring: Type basestring cannot be instantiated; it is the base for str and unicode.
      • __builtin__.unicode: unicode(string [, encoding[, errors]]) -> object
        • sqltriples.Special
          • sqltriples.Literal
          • sqltriples.Namespace
          • sqltriples.URIRef
    • __builtin__.type: type(object) -> the object's type type(name, bases, dict) -> a new type
  • sqltriples.BNode
  • sqltriples.Results: A class representing a selection of results.
    • sqltriples.CountableResults: A class representing a count of some results.
    • sqltriples.SingleResults: A class representing a selection of single value results.
      • sqltriples.Objects: A class representing a selection of objects.
      • sqltriples.Predicates: A class representing a selection of predicates.
      • sqltriples.Subjects: A class representing a selection of subjects.
    • sqltriples.Triples: A class representing a selection of triples.
  • sqltriples.Subject: A class representing a more conveniently accessible subject.
  • sqltriples.TripleStore: A triple store whose contents are stored in an SQL-accessible database table.
